discord-mcp-bridge
==================

This product includes software derived from the Discord plugin shipped with
Claude Code's `claude-plugins-official` marketplace
(https://docs.claude.com/en/docs/claude-code/plugins), version 0.0.4.

Original work © Anthropic PBC, licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0
(see LICENSE).

Modifications by the discord-mcp-bridge contributors:

- Added optional `DISCORD_TMUX_TARGET` environment variable. When set, inbound
  Discord messages that pass the access gate are also injected as keystrokes
  into the named tmux session (using `tmux send-keys -l`, literal mode, to
  prevent key-name interpretation). This lets AI CLIs that don't subscribe to
  the `notifications/claude/channel` MCP server-push notification (e.g. OpenAI
  Codex CLI) react to Discord messages when run as a tmux daemon.
- Updated header comment to reflect the bridge purpose.
- Repository-level changes: this NOTICE, fork-specific README, .gitignore.

The original Anthropic notification path (`mcp.notification`) is preserved
unchanged, so Claude Code remains a first-class consumer of this server.
